args:
At Aldred's advisement, the group has been
making its way to the Halidom. But in the midst
of the journey, Farren's friend Jake appears and
reveals himself as a Syndicate assassin—and
when he lays Aldred low, it steels Farren's
resolve to fight his new enemy all the more.
Wait, please... I can't run anymore...\nLet me rest...

I would very much like to do that for you,
but we cannot stop. We have miles yet to
cover if we want to escape the vigilant eye
of the Syndicate.
I don't care! My legs won't move!
Can't we rest, Grace? Just for a bit?\nThese people are all in really bad shape.
Let 'em rest if they want to, Grace.\nIt doesn't matter to me.
There's no way a group this size is going to\nescape the Syndicate's eye—which means\nit's the perfect decoy.

If the Syndicate shows up for these folks,
that just makes it easier for me to kill 'em.
And if a few of you happen to die, it's no
skin off my nose.
That's an awful thing to say!
I had no obligation to rescue you people\nfrom that facility. I owe you nothing.
But you both said you'd guide us\nsomewhere safe!
No, I just said you'd be safe if you made it\nto the Halidom. I didn't say anything about\nus playing babysitter the whole way there.
Look, you can do whatever you want,\nbut I vote for the ＂wait here and serve\nas bait option.＂
Damn it, fine! I'll keep walking!
There are a few locations ahead where we\nshould be able to secret ourselves away.\nTry to hold on until then.
Um, excuse me? Aldred? I just want to say\nthat I'm sorry about earlier.
You aren't as cruel as you seem. You just\nacted that way so we'd start walking again.
It was my duty to protect everyone, and I'm\nnot doing a very good job of it. So I just\nwanted to say thank you.
It's Farren, right? Tell me something,\nFarren: Do you hate the Syndicate?
If you were a captive of the Syndicate,\nthen you can't have had a pleasant time.\nYou must want revenge, right?

Hmm... Well, I DO want to stop the awful
things they're doing, but I think that's
different from, like, hating them or trying
to get revenge.

I did have a horrible time at the Syndicate.
The people I met would die one by one,
with me always ending up the one to
survive somehow.
And I know they all had people in their\nlives who loved them.
So I guess I'm fighting to help the people\nwho are left and to honor the memory of\nthose who are gone. Not revenge.
Huh. That ain't like me at all.

I hate the Syndicate. Hate 'em. They stole
my family, remade my body, and took
everything from me. The only thing I
wanted was revenge.
Now I walk a different path. Not one\nof revenge, although that hatred still\nburns within me.
I'm able to fight the Syndicate BECAUSE of\nmy hate. Once that burns out...there\nprobably won't be much of me left.
So don't end up like me, kid. You want to\nwalk a different path? Good. Stay on it.

But you can't be too soft. If you're
gonna fight the Syndicate, you gotta set
compassion aside from time to time
unless you want to end up in the dirt.
Right! In that case, just keep teaching\nme whatever I need to know!
Pass. I ain't the teaching type.
Come on, why not? You're my wyrmbinding\nbig brother—you gotta teach me!
I'm not even sure how to deal with this\nkind of chipper attitude...
How the heck are you even here, Jake?\nI thought the Syndicate killed you!

Somebody attacked the Syndicate facility
and I managed to get away in the chaos.
Can't believe I ran into you again all the
way out here.
Well, this is great! We're all trying to get\nsomewhere safe, so you gotta come!

Hang on. We took all the surviving
prisoners with us—I made sure of that.
So how did you manage to slip both us
and the Syndicate?
What are you talking about, Aldred?
Remember what I said about not being\nsoft? Well, you can start right here.\nI think this guy's a spy.
No! He's my friend! We were in that\nfacility together and he tried to help me\nbust everyone out!
Come on, Jake. Let's go see the others.
No, Jake! What are you doing?!
I knew it! This guy's a Syndicate assassin!
Sorry about the double-cross, little duck,\nbut I've got ranks to climb and killing that\nneeds done to do it.
Jake, no! This can't be happening!
Not if I have anything to say about it.
Huh? The hell? My wyrmbinding power\nwon't activate!
That's because I've poisoned you with\na compound that stops your powers.\nTerribly sorry, but it's time to die!
Pulling me down this cliff won't save you!\nWe'll just die together!
Yeah, I think I'm good with that...\nTake care of those people, Farren!
You know, the person I once was couldn't\nprotect a single damn thing...
So go be the guardian I could never be.
It's Aldred! He... It's all my fault!
Heh heh. For a lab rat, that one performed\nsurprisingly well in eliminating Tf-997.
They found us... Farren, I need you to go to\nthe others and get them out of here.
No! Aldred told me I needed to protect\nthem, so I'm going to fight!
C'mon, Lil' Barb! Let's do this!
